<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" xmlns:html="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="id80ecda1d-3a70-11f1-b817-c08bf6d1fe2c" identifier="/us/usc/t40/s18101"><num value="18101">§ 18101.</num><heading> Definitions</heading>
<chapeau style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">In this chapter—</chapeau><paragraph style="-uslm-lc:I12" class="indent1" id="id80ecda1e-3a70-11f1-b817-c08bf6d1fe2c" identifier="/us/usc/t40/s18101/1"><num value="1">(1)</num><heading> <inline class="small-caps">Federal agency</inline>.—</heading><content>The term “federal agency” has the same meaning given that term in <ref href="/us/usc/t40/s102">section 102 of this title</ref>.</content>
</paragraph>
<paragraph style="-uslm-lc:I12" class="indent1" id="id80ecda1f-3a70-11f1-b817-c08bf6d1fe2c" identifier="/us/usc/t40/s18101/2"><num value="2">(2)</num><heading> TTY.—</heading><content>The term “TTY” means a text-telephone used in the transmission of coded signals through the nationwide telecommunications system.</content>
</paragraph>
<sourceCredit id="id80ecda20-3a70-11f1-b817-c08bf6d1fe2c">(<ref href="/us/pl/107/217">Pub. L. 107–217</ref>, <date date="2002-08-21">Aug. 21, 2002</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/116/1290">116 Stat. 1290</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
